'''Bohumil Brhel'''<!-- (born [[]], 19)--> is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[Motorcycle speedway|speedway]] rider and he won the  [[2001 Individual Speedway European Championship|2001 Individual European Champion]] title.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.speedwaya-z.cz/view.php?cisloclanku=2007100501|title=Bohumil Brhel v pond<U+011B>l<U+00ED> ofici<U+00E1>ln<U+011B> ukon<U+010D><U+00ED> kari<U+00E9>ru|date=2007-10-05|publisher=speedwaya-z.cz|language=Czech|accessdate=14 June 2010}}</ref> He won the Czechoslovakian title on six occasions

==Career==
===World Final Appearances===
* [[1989 Individual Speedway World Championship|1989]] - {{flagicon|GER}} [[Munich]], [[Olympic Stadium (Munich)|Olympic Stadium]] - 16th - 1pt
*[[1994 Individual Speedway World Championship|1994]] - {{flagicon|DEN}} [[Vojens]], [[Vojens Speedway Center]] - 10th - 6pts

